<p id="p0250">The electronic 
 <xref rid="fd22" ref-type="disp-formula">Eq. (22)</xref> is solved by perturbation theory with the perturbation operator
 <disp-formula id="fd25">
  <label>(25)</label>
  <math id="M108" altimg="si93.svg" alttext="Equation 25.">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mover accent="true">
      <mi>U</mi>
      <mo>˜</mo>
     </mover>
    </mrow>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak">≡</mo>
    <munder>
     <mo movablelimits="false">∑</mo>
     <mrow>
      <mi>ι</mi>
     </mrow>
    </munder>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mrow>
       <mi>U</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <mi>ι</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mrow>
      <mo stretchy="true">(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mi mathvariant="bold">q</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo stretchy="true">)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mo stretchy="true">(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mrow>
         <mi>p</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mi>ι</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo linebreak="badbreak">−</mo>
       <msub>
        <mrow>
         <mover accent="true">
          <mi>p</mi>
          <mo>˜</mo>
         </mover>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
         <mi>ι</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mo stretchy="true">)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
    <mtext>,</mtext>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>similar to the perturbation operator of Pekar [
 <xref rid="bib73" ref-type="bibr">73</xref>, 
 <xref rid="bib74" ref-type="bibr">74</xref>]. It will be shown below that 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M109" altimg="si94.svg">
   <mrow>
    <msub>
     <mrow>
      <mover accent="true">
       <mi>p</mi>
       <mo>˜</mo>
      </mover>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi>ι</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> are the values of the normal phonon coordinates for which the adiabatic potential in 
 <xref rid="fd24" ref-type="disp-formula">Eq. (24)</xref> has a minimum.
</p>
